7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 325, L.D. 496, “An Act Regarding the
10 Time Frame for Issuing a Silver Alert and to Require Silver Alerts for All Persons Missing
11 from Certain Inpatient Facilities”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act Regarding the Issuance of Silver Alerts'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §2202, as amended by PL 2021, c. 62, §2, is further amended to
17 read:
18 §2202. Silver Alert Program
19 In accordance with this chapter and with the cooperation of the Department of
20 Transportation, the Maine Turnpike Authority, a statewide organization representing
21 broadcast groups in the State, the Office of the Governor and appropriate law enforcement
22 agencies, the department shall develop and implement the Silver Alert Program to be
23 activated on behalf of missing endangered persons. The program must include standards
24 of procedure for local law enforcement agencies to determine that a missing person is a
25 missing endangered person, to determine information to be released regarding the missing
26 endangered person or the circumstances of the person's disappearance and to appropriately
27 activate a Silver Alert to local or statewide law enforcement agencies and to the media, a
28 plan for providing relevant information to the public through an existing system of dynamic
29 message signs located across the State when necessary and training for all law enforcement
30 officers. The Silver Alert Program must require that all Silver Alerts be issued to all
31 hospitals and homeless shelters in the State and to a statewide association of libraries. The
32 Silver Alert Program must be developed and implemented using existing resources.'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
